items.title: Crew Studies Cardiac Health and Unpacks Cygnus, Progress Spacecraft - NASA
items.content_text: Expedition 73 kicked off the week with ultrasound scans for cardiac research and unloading new science experiments delivered last week aboard the Cygnus XL cargo craft. Spacesuit work and computer networking maintenance rounded out the day aboard the International Space Station.

items.title: NASA, Northrop Grumman Collaboration Ensures Resupply Mission Success - NASA
items.content_text: The crew aboard the International Space Station continue to unpack more than 11,000 pounds of critical spares, food and supplies delivered Sept. 18 by a Cygnus XL commercial resupply mission.  The arrival of the Cygnus XL to the space station was delayed by one day, due to changes in the rendezvous planning resulting from the main spacecraft engine shutting down early on two burns on Sept. 16.

items.title: NASA’s Deep Space Communications Demo Exceeds Project Expectations
items.content_text: The project has exceeded all of its technical goals after two years, setting up the foundations of high-speed communications for NASA’s future human missions to Mars.

items.title: NASA’s Tally of Planets Outside Our Solar System Reaches 6,000
items.content_text: The milestone highlights the accelerating rate of discoveries, just over three decades since the first exoplanets were found.

items.title: NASA Analysis Shows Sun’s Activity Ramping Up
items.content_text: It looked like the Sun was heading toward a historic lull in activity. That trend flipped in 2008, according to new research.

items.title: NASA’s GUARDIAN Tsunami Detection Tech Catches Wave in Real Time
items.content_text: A massive earthquake and subsequent tsunami off Russia in late July tested an experimental detection system that had deployed a critical component just the day before.

items.title: New U.S.-European Sea Level Satellite Will Help Safeguard Ships at Sea
items.content_text: Sea surface height data from the Sentinel-6B satellite, led by NASA and ESA, will help with the development of marine weather forecasts, alerting ships to possible dangers.

items.title: NASA Says Mars Rover Discovered Potential Biosignature Last Year
items.content_text: After a year’s worth of scientific scrutiny, the ‘Sapphire Canyon’ rock sample remains the mission’s best candidate for containing signs of ancient microbial life processes.

items.title: NASA to Share Details of New Perseverance Mars Rover Finding
items.content_text: A news conference this morning will focus on the analysis of a rock sampled by the agency’s Perseverance Mars rover last year, which is the subject of a forthcoming science paper.

items.title: NASA Study: Celestial ‘Accident’ Sheds Light on Jupiter, Saturn Riddle
items.content_text: An unusual cosmic object is helping scientists better understand the chemistry hidden deep in Jupiter and Saturn’s atmospheres — and potentially those of exoplanets.

items.title: NASA-ISRO Satellite Lifts Off to Track Earth’s Changing Surfaces
items.content_text: The first-of-its kind satellite will provide actionable information in a range of areas, including disaster response, infrastructure monitoring, and agricultural management.

items.title: Blue Origin Completes 35th New Shepard Mission | Blue Origin
items.content_text: Blue Origin successfully completed its 35th New Shepard flight and 15th payload mission today from Launch Site One in West Texas.

items.title: Blue Alchemist Hits Major Milestone Toward Permanent and Sustainable Lunar Infrastructure | Blue Origin
items.content_text: Blue Origin's pioneering in-space resource utilization system, Blue Alchemist, has successfully completed its Critical Design Review, marking a transformative milestone toward humanity's permanent expansion beyond Earth.

items.title: The Mission: Blue Origin’s Mars Telecommunications Orbiter | Blue Origin
items.content_text: Built upon our existing and affordable Blue Ring platform, our Mars Telecommunications Orbiter is ready to support NASA’s Mars mission in 2028.

items.title: Blue Origin’s New Shepard Completes 34th Mission to Space | Blue Origin
